{"title": "Over the Top", "description": "Arthur Guy Empey was an American who responded to the sinking of the Lusitania by enlisting with the British Army to fight in France. His experiences in the trenches, including his ultimate wounding and convalescence, became this book. When published in 1917, it was a major hit and helped the recruiting effort when America entered the Great War.<br /><br />If you've heard of the horror of trench warfare in WWI and want to see it from below dirt level, Empey offers it all here.<br /><br />Also included is Empey's popular \"Tommy's Dictionary of the Trenches\" which humorously demystifies the slang used by the British soldier. (Summary by Mark F. Smith)", "duration": 25456, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2600", "name": "Arthur Guy Empey"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt4/Over_the_Top_1004.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["War & Military", "Memoirs"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mark F. Smith"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mark F. Smith"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ans Wink"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Dedication, Foreword, and Glossary 1", "readers": [204], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/overthetop_0812_librivox/overthetop_01_empey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2832}, {"section": 2, "title": "Glossary Part 2", "readers": [204], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/overthetop_0812_librivox/overthetop_02_empey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2494}, {"section": 3, "title": "Ch. 1 \u2013 From Mufti to Khaki; Ch. 2 \u2013 Blighty to Reat Billets", "readers": [204], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/overthetop_0812_librivox/overthetop_03_empey_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1759}, {"section": 4, "title": "Ch. 3 \u2013 I Go to Church; Ch. 4 \u2013 Into the Trench", "readers": [204], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/overthetop_0812_librivox/overthetop_04_empey_64kb.mp